    "body": "### Problem\n\n`client:stop(number)` seems to behave identically to `client:stop(true)`. A possible bug in #36378.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- Take an existing lsp and modify its source code so it ignores shutdown requests. I used the python-lanaguage-server for this. You'll know the modifications work correctly when `:stop()` fails to stop the server.\n- Run `:stop(5000)`, or pick any other large number.\n- The server will stop instantaneously.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect the server to not be terminated until the timeout is reached.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev+1562-02cd56489\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.43.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nNeovim Nightly COPR repo",
